biology: Its shell is as hard as sheet rock, and it is also very strong. Its THRASHING can topple a mountain.

name: tyranitar
biology: Its body can't be harmed by any sort of attack, so it is very eager to make challenges against enemies.

name: lugia
biology: It is said that it quietly spends its time deep at the bottom of the sea because its powers are too strong.

name: ho-oh
biology: Legends claim this POKéMON flies the world's skies con­ tinuously on its magnificent seven- colored wings.

name: celebi
biology: This POKéMON wan­ ders across time. Grass and trees flourish in the forests in which it has appeared.

name: treecko
biology: TREECKO has small hooks on the bottom of its feet that enable it to scale vertical walls. This POKéMON attacks by slamming foes with its thick tail.

name: grovyle
biology: The leaves growing out of GROVYLE’s body are convenient for camouflaging it from enemies in the forest. This POKéMON is a master at climbing trees in jungles.

name: sceptile
biology: The leaves growing on SCEPTILE’s body are very sharp edged. This POKéMON is very agile - it leaps all over the branches of trees and jumps on its foe from above or behind.

name: torchic
biology: TORCHIC sticks with its TRAINER, following behind with unsteady steps. This POKéMON breathes fire of over 1,800 degrees F, including fireballs that leave the foe scorched black.

name: combusken
biology: COMBUSKEN toughens up its legs and thighs by running through fields and mountains. This POKéMON’s legs possess both speed and power, enabling it to dole out ten kicks in one second.

name: blaziken
biology: In battle, BLAZIKEN blows out intense flames from its wrists and attacks foes courageously. The stronger the foe, the more intensely this POKéMON’s wrists burn.

name: mudkip
biology: The fin on MUDKIP’s head acts as highly sensitive radar. Using this fin to sense movements of water and air, this POKéMON can determine what is taking place around it without using its eyes.

name: marshtomp
biology: The surface of MARSHTOMP’s body is enveloped by a thin, sticky film that enables it to live on land. This POKéMON plays in mud on beaches when the ocean tide is low.

name: swampert
biology: SWAMPERT is very strong. It has enough power to easily drag a boulder weighing more than a ton. This POKéMON also has powerful vision that lets it see even in murky water.

name: poochyena
biology: At first sight, POOCHYENA takes a bite at anything that moves. This POKéMON chases after prey until the victim becomes exhausted. However, it may turn tail if the prey strikes back.

name: mightyena
biology: MIGHTYENA gives obvious signals when it is preparing to attack. It starts to growl deeply and then flattens its body. This POKéMON will bite savagely with its sharply pointed fangs.

name: zigzagoon
biology: ZIGZAGOON restlessly wanders everywhere at all times. This POKéMON does so because it is very curious. It becomes interested in anything that it happens to see.

name: linoone
biology: LINOONE always runs full speed and only in straight lines. If facing an obstacle, it makes a right-angle turn to evade it. This POKéMON is very challenged by gently curving roads.

name: wurmple
biology: Using the spikes on its rear end,   WURMPLE peels the bark off trees and feeds on the sap that oozes out. This POKéMON’s feet are tipped with suction pads that allow it to cling to glass without slipping.

name: silcoon
biology: SILCOON tethers itself to a tree branch using silk to keep from falling. There,  this POKéMON hangs quietly while it awaits evolution. It peers out of the silk cocoon through a small hole.

name: beautifly
biology: BEAUTIFLY’s favorite food is the sweet pollen of flowers. If you want to see this POKéMON, just leave a potted flower by an open window. BEAUTIFLY is sure to come looking for pollen.

name: cascoon
biology: CASCOON makes its protective cocoon by wrapping its body entirely with a fine silk from its mouth. Once the silk goes around its body, it hardens. This POKéMON prepares for its evolution inside the cocoon.

name: dustox
biology: DUSTOX is instinctively drawn to light. Swarms of this POKéMON are attracted by the bright lights of cities, where they wreak havoc by stripping the leaves off roadside trees for food.

name: lotad
biology: LOTAD live in ponds and lakes, where they float on the surface. It grows weak if its broad leaf dies. On rare occasions, this POKéMON travels on land in search of clean water.

name: lombre
biology: LOMBRE is nocturnal - it will get active after dusk. It is also a mischief-maker. When this POKéMON spots anglers, it tugs on their fishing lines from beneath the surface and enjoys their consternation.

name: ludicolo
biology: LUDICOLO begins dancing as soon as it hears cheerful, festive music. This POKéMON is said to appear when it hears the singing of children on hiking outings.

name: seedot
biology: SEEDOT attaches itself to a tree branch using the top of its head. It sucks moisture from the tree while hanging off the branch. The more water it drinks, the glossier this POKéMON’s body becomes.

name: nuzleaf
biology: NUZLEAF live in densely overgrown forests. They occasionally venture out of the forest to startle people. This POKéMON dislikes having its long nose pinched.

name: shiftry
biology: SHIFTRY is a mysterious POKéMON that is said to live atop towering trees  dating back over a thousand years. It creates terrific windstorms with the fans it holds.

name: taillow
biology: TAILLOW courageously stands its ground against foes, however strong they may be. This gutsy POKéMON will remain defiant even after a loss. On the other hand, it cries loudly if it becomes hungry.

name: swellow
biology: SWELLOW flies high above our heads, making graceful arcs in the sky. This POKéMON dives at a steep angle as soon as it spots its prey. The hapless prey is tightly grasped by SWELLOW’s clawed feet, preventing escape.

name: wingull
biology: WINGULL has the habit of carrying prey and valuables in its beak and hiding them in all sorts of locations. This POKéMON rides the winds and flies as if it were skating across the sky.

name: pelipper
biology: PELIPPER is a flying transporter that carries small POKéMON and eggs inside its massive bill. This POKéMON builds its nest on steep cliffs facing the sea.

name: ralts
biology: RALTS senses the emotions of people using the horns on its head. This POKéMON rarely appears before people. But when it does, it draws closer if it senses that the person has a positive disposition.

name: kirlia
biology: It is said that a KIRLIA that is exposed to the positive emotions of its TRAINER grows beautiful. This POKéMON controls psychokinetic powers with its highly developed brain.

name: gardevoir
biology: GARDEVOIR has the ability to read the future. If it senses impending danger to its TRAINER, this POKéMON is said to unleash its psychokinetic energy at full power.

name: surskit
biology: From the tips of its feet, SURSKIT secretes an oil that enables it to walk on water as if it were skating. This POKéMON feeds on microscopic organisms in ponds and lakes.

name: masquerain
biology: MASQUERAIN intimidates enemies with the eyelike patterns on its antennas. This POKéMON flaps its four wings to freely fly in any direction - even sideways and backwards - as if it were a helicopter.

name: shroomish
biology: SHROOMISH live in damp soil in the dark depths of forests. They are often found keeping still under fallen leaves. This POKéMON feeds on compost that is made up of fallen, rotted leaves.

name: breloom
biology: BRELOOM closes in on its foe with light and sprightly footwork, then throws punches with its stretchy arms. This POKéMON’s fighting technique puts boxers to shame.

name: slakoth
biology: SLAKOTH lolls around for over twenty hours every day. Because it moves so little, it does not need much food. This POKéMON’s sole daily meal consists of just three leaves.

name: vigoroth
biology: VIGOROTH is always itching and agitated to go on a wild rampage. It simply can’t tolerate sitting still for even a minute. This POKéMON’s stress level rises if it can’t be moving constantly.

name: slaking
biology: SLAKING spends all day lying down and lolling about. It eats grass growing within its reach. If it eats all the grass it can reach, this POKéMON reluctantly moves to another spot.

name: nincada
biology: NINCADA lives underground for many years in complete darkness. This POKéMON absorbs nutrients from the roots of trees. It stays motionless as it waits for evolution.

name: ninjask
biology: NINJASK moves around at such a high speed that it cannot be seen, even while its crying can be clearly heard. For that reason, this POKéMON was long believed to be invisible.

name: shedinja
biology: A discarded bug shell that came to life. Peering into the crack on its back is said to steal one’s spirit.

name: whismur
biology: Normally, WHISMUR’s voice is very quiet - it is barely audible even if one is paying close attention. However, if this POKéMON senses danger, it starts crying at an earsplitting volume.

name: loudred
biology: LOUDRED’s bellowing can completely decimate a wood-frame house. It uses its voice to punish its foes. This POKéMON’s round ears serve as loudspeakers.

name: exploud
biology: EXPLOUD triggers earthquakes with the tremors it creates by bellowing. If this POKéMON violently inhales from the ports on its body, it’s a sign that it is preparing to let loose a huge bellow.

name: makuhita
biology: MAKUHITA is tenacious - it will keep getting up and attacking its foe however many times it is knocked down. Every time it gets back up, this POKéMON stores more energy in its body for evolving.

name: hariyama
biology: HARIYAMA practices its straight-arm slaps in any number of locations. One hit of this POKéMON’s powerful, openhanded, straight-arm punches could snap a telephone pole in two.

name: azurill
biology: AZURILL spins its tail as if it were a lasso, then hurls it far. The momentum of the throw sends its body flying, too. Using this unique action, one of these POKéMON managed to hurl itself a record 33 feet.

name: nosepass
biology: NOSEPASS’s magnetic nose is always pointed to the north. If two of these POKéMON meet, they cannot turn their faces to each other when they are close because their magnetic noses repel one another.

name: skitty
biology: SKITTY has the habit of becoming fascinated by moving objects and chasing them around. This POKéMON is known to chase after its own tail and become dizzy.

name: delcatty
biology: DELCATTY prefers to live an unfettered existence in which it can do as it pleases at its own pace. Because this POKéMON eats and sleeps whenever it decides, its daily routines are completely random.

name: sableye
biology: SABLEYE lead quiet lives deep inside caverns. They are feared, however, because these POKéMON are thought to steal the spirits of people when their eyes burn with a sinister glow in the darkness.

name: mawile
biology: MAWHILE’s huge jaws are actually steel horns that have been transformed. Its docile-looking face serves to lull its foe into letting down its guard. When the foe least expects it, MAWHILE chomps it with its gaping jaws.

name: aron
biology: This POKéMON has a body of steel. To make its body, ARON feeds on iron ore that it digs from mountains. Occasionally, it causes major trouble by eating bridges and rails.

name: lairon
biology: LAIRON tempers its steel body by drinking highly nutritious mineral springwater until it is bloated. This POKéMON makes its nest close to springs of delicious water.

name: aggron
biology: AGGRON claims an entire mountain as its own territory. It mercilessly beats up anything that violates its environment. This POKéMON vigilantly patrols its territory at all times.

name: meditite
biology: MEDITITE undertakes rigorous mental training deep in the mountains. However, whenever it meditates, this POKéMON always loses its concentration and focus. As a result, its training never ends.

name: medicham
biology: It is said that through meditation, MEDICHAM heightens energy inside its body and sharpens its sixth sense. This POKéMON hides its presence by merging itself with fields and mountains.

name: electrike
biology: ELECTRIKE stores electricity in its long body hair. This POKéMON stimulates its leg muscles with electric charges. These jolts of power give its legs explosive acceleration performance.

name: manectric
biology: It rarely appears before people. It is said to nest where lightning has fallen.

name: plusle
biology: PLUSLE always acts as a cheerleader for its partners. Whenever a teammate puts out a good effort in battle, this POKéMON shorts out its body to create the crackling noises of sparks to show its joy.

name: minun
biology: MINUN is more concerned about cheering on its partners than its own safety. It shorts out the electricity in its body to create brilliant showers of sparks to cheer on its teammates.

name: volbeat
biology: With the arrival of night, VOLBEAT emits light from its tail. It communicates with others by adjusting the intensity and flashing of its light. This POKéMON is attracted by the sweet aroma of ILLUMISE.

name: illumise
biology: ILLUMISE attracts a swarm of VOLBEAT using a sweet fragrance. Once the VOLBEAT have gathered, this POKéMON leads the lit-up swarm in drawing geometric designs on the canvas of the night sky.

name: roselia
biology: ROSELIA shoots sharp thorns as projectiles at any opponent that tries to steal the flowers on its arms. The aroma of this POKéMON brings serenity to living things.

name: gulpin
biology: Virtually all of GULPIN’s body is its stomach. As a result, it can swallow something its own size. This POKéMON’s stomach contains a special fluid that digests anything.

name: swalot
biology: It swallows anything whole. It sweats toxic fluids from its follicles to douse foes.

name: carvanha
biology: CARVANHA’s strongly developed jaws and its sharply pointed fangs pack the destructive power to rip out boat hulls. Many boats have been attacked and sunk by this POKéMON.

name: sharpedo
biology: Nicknamed “the bully of the sea,” SHARPEDO is widely feared. Its cruel fangs grow back immediately if they snap off. Just one of these POKéMON can thoroughly tear apart a supertanker.

name: wailmer
biology: It bounces playfully like a ball. The more seawater it swallows, the higher it bounces.

name: wailord
biology: WAILORD is the largest of all identified POKéMON up to now. This giant POKéMON swims languorously in the vast open sea, eating massive amounts of food at once with its enormous mouth.

name: numel
biology: NUMEL is extremely dull witted - it doesn’t notice being hit. However, it can’t stand hunger for even a second. This POKéMON’s body is a seething cauldron of boiling magma.

name: camerupt
biology: CAMERUPT has a volcano inside its body. Magma of 18,000 degrees F courses through its body. Occasionally, the humps on this POKéMON’s back erupt, spewing the superheated magma.

name: torkoal
biology: TORKOAL digs through mountains in search of coal. If it finds some, it fills hollow spaces on its shell with the coal and burns it. If it is attacked, this POKéMON spouts thick black smoke to beat a retreat.

name: spoink
biology: SPOINK bounces around on its tail. The shock of its bouncing makes its heart pump. As a result, this POKéMON cannot afford to stop bouncing - if it stops, its heart will stop.

name: grumpig
biology: GRUMPIG uses the black pearls on its body to amplify its psychic power waves for gaining total control over its foe. When this POKéMON uses its special power, its snorting breath grows labored.

name: spinda
biology: All the SPINDA that exist in the world are said to have utterly unique spot patterns. The shaky, tottering steps of this POKéMON give it the appearance of dancing.

name: trapinch
biology: Its big jaws crunch through boulders. Because its head is so big, it has a hard time getting back upright if it tips over onto its back.

name: vibrava
biology: To make prey faint, VIBRAVA generates ultrasonic waves by vigorously making its two wings vibrate. This POKéMON’s ultrasonic waves are so powerful, they can bring on headaches in people.

name: flygon
biology: FLYGON is nicknamed “the elemental  spirit of the desert.” Because its flapping wings whip up a cloud of sand, this POKéMON is always enveloped in a sandstorm while flying.

name: cacnea
biology: CACNEA lives in arid locations such as deserts. It releases a strong aroma from its flower to attract prey. When prey comes near, this POKéMON shoots sharp thorns from its body to bring the victim down.

name: cacturne
biology: During the daytime, CACTURNE remains unmoving so that it does not lose any moisture to the harsh desert sun. This POKéMON becomes active at night when the temperature drops.

name: swablu
biology: SWABLU has light and fluffy wings that are like cottony clouds. This POKéMON is not frightened of people. It lands on the heads of people and sits there like a cotton-fluff hat.

name: altaria
biology: ALTARIA dances and wheels through the sky among billowing, cotton-like clouds. By singing melodies in its crystal-clear voice, this POKéMON makes its listeners experience dreamy wonderment.

name: zangoose
biology: Memories of battling its arch-rival SEVIPER are etched into every cell of ZANGOOSE’s body. This POKéMON adroitly dodges attacks with incredible agility.

name: seviper
biology: SEVIPER shares a generations-long feud with ZANGOOSE. The scars on its body are evidence of vicious battles. This POKéMON attacks using its sword- edged tail.

name: lunatone
biology: LUNATONE was discovered at a location where a meteorite fell. As a result, some people theorize that this POKéMON came from space. However, no one has been able to prove this theory so far.

name: solrock
biology: SOLROCK is a new species of POKéMON that is said to have fallen from space. It floats in air and moves silently. In battle, this POKéMON releases intensely bright light.

name: barboach
biology: BARBOACH’s sensitive whiskers serve as a superb radar system. This POKéMON hides in mud, leaving only its two whiskers exposed while it waits for prey to come along.

name: whiscash
biology: WHISCASH is extremely territorial. Just one of these POKéMON will claim a large pond as its exclusive territory. If a foe approaches it, it thrashes about and triggers a massive earthquake.

name: corphish
biology: CORPHISH were originally foreign POKéMON that were imported as pets. They eventually turned up in the wild. This POKéMON is very hardy and has greatly increased its population.

name: crawdaunt
biology: CRAWDAUNT has an extremely violent nature that compels it to challenge other living things to battle. Other life-forms refuse to live in ponds inhabited by this POKéMON, making them desolate places.

name: baltoy
biology: BALTOY moves while spinning around on its one foot. Primitive wall paintings depicting this POKéMON living among people were discovered in some ancient ruins.

name: claydol
biology: CLAYDOL are said to be dolls of mud made by primitive humans and brought to life by exposure to a mysterious ray. This POKéMON moves about while levitating.

name: lileep
biology: LILEEP became extinct approximately a hundred million years ago. This ancient POKéMON attaches itself to a rock on the seafloor and catches approaching prey using tentacles  shaped like flower petals.

name: cradily
biology: CRADILY roams around the ocean floor in search of food. This POKéMON freely extends its tree trunk-like neck and captures unwary prey using its eight tentacles.

name: anorith
biology: ANORITH was regenerated from a prehistoric fossil. This primitive POKéMON once lived in warm seas. It grips its prey firmly between its two large claws.

name: armaldo
biology: ARMALDO’s tough armor makes all attacks bounce off. This POKéMON’s two enormous claws can be freely extended or contracted. They have the power to punch right through a steel slab.

name: feebas
biology: FEEBAS’s fins are ragged and tattered from the start of its life. Because of its shoddy appearance, this POKéMON is largely ignored. It is capable of living in both the sea and in rivers.

name: milotic
biology: MILOTIC is said to be the most beautiful of all the POKéMON. It has the power to becalm such emotions as anger and hostility to quell bitter feuding.

name: castform
biology: CASTFORM’s appearance changes with the weather. This POKéMON gained the ability to use the vast power of nature to protect its tiny body.

name: kecleon
biology: KECLEON is capable of changing its body colors at will to blend in with its surroundings. There is one exception - this POKéMON can’t change the zigzag pattern on its belly.

name: shuppet
biology: SHUPPET is attracted by feelings of jealousy and vindictiveness. If someone develops strong feelings of vengeance, this POKéMON will appear in a swarm and line up beneath the eaves of that person’s home.

name: banette
biology: BANETTE generates energy for laying strong curses by sticking pins into its own body. This POKéMON was originally a pitiful plush doll that was thrown away.

name: duskull
biology: DUSKULL can pass through any wall no matter how thick it may be. Once this POKéMON chooses a target, it will doggedly pursue the intended victim until the break of dawn.

name: dusclops
biology: DUSCLOPS’s body is completely hollow - there is nothing at all inside. It is said that its body is like a black hole. This POKéMON will absorb anything into its body, but nothing will ever come back out.

name: tropius
biology: The bunches of fruit around TROPIUS’s neck are very popular with children. This POKéMON loves fruit, and eats it continuously. Apparently, its love for fruit resulted in its own outgrowth of fruit.

name: chimecho
biology: Emitting ultrasonic cries, it floats on winds to travel great distances.

name: absol
biology: Every time ABSOL appears before people, it is followed by a disaster such as an earthquake or a tidal wave. As a result, it came to be known as the disaster POKéMON.

name: wynaut
biology: WYNAUT can always be seen with a big, happy smile on its face. Look at its tail to determine if it is angry. When angered, this POKéMON will be slapping the ground with its tail.

name: snorunt
biology: SNORUNT live in regions with heavy snowfall. In seasons without snow, such as spring and summer, this POKéMON steals away to live quietly among stalactites and stalagmites deep in caverns.

name: glalie
biology: GLALIE has a body made of rock, which it hardens with an armor of ice. This POKéMON has the ability to freeze moisture in the atmosphere into any shape it desires.

name: spheal
biology: SPHEAL is much faster rolling than  walking to get around. When groups of this POKéMON eat, they all clap at once to show their pleasure. Because of this, their mealtimes are noisy.

name: sealeo
biology: SEALEO has the habit of always juggling on the tip of its nose anything it sees for the first time. This POKéMON occasionally entertains itself by balancing and rolling a SPHEAL on its nose.

name: walrein
biology: WALREIN’s two massively developed tusks can totally shatter blocks of ice weighing ten tons with one blow. This POKéMON’s thick coat of blubber insulates it from subzero temperatures.

name: clamperl
biology: CLAMPERL’s sturdy shell is not only good for protection - it is also used for clamping and catching prey. A fully grown CLAMPERL’s shell will be scored with nicks and scratches all over.

name: huntail
biology: It lives deep in the pitch-dark sea. It attracts prey by moving its tail in mimicry of a small animal.

name: gorebyss
biology: GOREBYSS lives in the southern seas at extreme depths. Its body is built to withstand the enormous pressure of water at incredible depths. Because of this, this POKéMON’s body is unharmed by ordinary attacks.

name: relicanth
biology: It has remained unchanged for 100 million years. It was discovered during a deep-sea exploration.

name: luvdisc
biology: LUVDISC live in shallow seas in the tropics. This heart-shaped POKéMON earned its name by swimming after loving couples it spotted in the ocean’s waves.

name: bagon
biology: BAGON has a dream of one day soaring in the sky. In doomed efforts to fly, this POKéMON hurls itself off cliffs. As a result of its dives, its head has  grown tough and as hard as tempered steel.

name: shelgon
biology: Inside SHELGON’s armor-like shell, cells are in the midst of transformation to create an entirely new body. This POKéMON’s shell is extremely heavy, making its movements sluggish.

name: salamence
biology: SALAMENCE came about as a result of a strong, long-held dream of growing wings. It is said that this powerful desire triggered a sudden mutation in this POKéMON’s cells, causing it to sprout its magnificent wings.

name: beldum
biology: Its cells are all magnetic, and it communicates with others by using magnetic pulses.

name: metang
biology: When two BELDUM fuse together, METANG is formed. The brains of the BELDUM are joined by a magnetic nervous system. By linking its brains magnetically, this POKéMON generates strong psychokinetic power.

name: metagross
biology: METAGROSS has four brains in total. Combined, the four brains can breeze through difficult calculations faster than a supercomputer. This POKéMON can float in the air by tucking in its four legs.

name: regirock
biology: REGIROCK was sealed away by people long ago. If this POKéMON’s body is damaged in battle, it is said to seek out suitable rocks on its own to repair itself.

name: regice
biology: REGICE’s body was made during an ice age. The deep-frozen body can’t be melted, even by fire. This POKéMON controls frigid air of minus 328 degrees F.

name: registeel
biology: REGISTEEL has a body that is harder than any kind of metal. Its body is apparently hollow. No one has any idea what this POKéMON eats.

name: latias
biology: LATIAS is highly sensitive to the emotions of people. If it senses any hostility, this POKéMON ruffles the feathers all over its body and cries shrilly to intimidate the foe.

name: latios
biology: LATIOS has the ability to make its foe see an image of what it has seen or imagines in its head. This POKéMON is intelligent and understands human speech.

name: kyogre
biology: KYOGRE has the power to create massive rain clouds that cover the entire sky and bring about torrential downpours. This POKéMON saved people who were suffering from droughts.

name: groudon
biology: GROUDON has long been described in  mythology as the POKéMON that raised lands and expanded continents. This POKéMON took to sleep after a cataclysmic battle with KYOGRE.

name: rayquaza
biology: RAYQUAZA lived for hundreds of millions of years in the earth’s ozone layer,  never descending to the ground. This POKéMON appears to feed on water and particles in the atmosphere.

name: jirachi
biology: A legend states that JIRACHI will make true any wish that is written on notes attached to its head when it awakens. If this POKéMON senses danger, it will fight without awakening.

name: deoxys-normal
biology: The DNA of a space virus underwent a sudden mutation upon exposure to a laser beam and resulted in DEOXYS. The crystalline organ on this POKéMON’s chest appears to be its brain.

name: turtwig
biology: Made from soil, the shell on its back hardens when it drinks water. It lives along lakes.

name: grotle
biology: It lives along water in forests. In the daytime, it leaves the forest to sunbathe its treed shell.

name: torterra
biology: Small Pokémon occasionally gather on its unmoving back to begin building their nests.

name: chimchar
biology: It agilely scales sheer cliffs to live atop craggy mountains. Its fire is put out when it sleeps.

name: monferno
biology: To intimidate attackers, it stretches the fire on its tail to make itself appear bigger.

name: infernape
biology: It uses a special kind of martial arts involving all its limbs. Its fire never goes out.

name: piplup
biology: Because it is very proud, it hates accepting food from people. Its thick down guards it from cold.

name: prinplup
biology: It lives alone, away from others. Apparently, every one of them believes it is the most important.

name: empoleon
biology: The three horns that extend from its beak attest to its power. The leader has the biggest horns.

name: starly
biology: They flock in great numbers. Though small, they flap their wings with great power.

name: staravia
biology: It flies around forests and fields in search of bug Pokémon. It stays within a huge flock.

name: staraptor
biology: It has a savage nature. It will courageously challenge foes that are much larger.

name: bidoof
biology: With nerves of steel, nothing can perturb it. It is more agile and active than it appears.

name: bibarel
biology: It makes its nest by damming streams with bark and mud. It is known as an industrious worker.

name: kricketot
biology: It shakes its head back to front, causing its antennae to hit each other and sound like a xylophone.

name: kricketune
biology: It crosses its knifelike arms in front of its chest when it cries. It can compose melodies ad lib.

name: shinx
biology: All of its fur dazzles if danger is sensed. It flees while the foe is momentarily blinded.

name: luxio
biology: Its claws loose electricity with enough amperage to cause fainting. They live in small groups.

name: luxray
biology: It has eyes that can see through anything. It spots and captures prey hiding behind objects.

name: budew
biology: Over the winter, it closes its bud and endures the cold. In spring, the bud opens and releases pollen.

name: roserade
biology: It attracts prey with a sweet aroma, then downs it with thorny whips hidden in its arms.

name: cranidos
biology: It lived in jungles around 100 million years ago. Its skull is as hard as iron.

name: rampardos
biology: Its powerful head butt has enough power to shatter even the most durable things upon impact.

name: shieldon
biology: A Pokémon that lived in jungles around 100 million years ago. Its facial hide is extremely hard.

name: bastiodon
biology: Any frontal attack is repulsed. It is a docile Pokémon that feeds on grass and berries.

name: burmy
biology: To shelter itself from cold, wintry winds, it covers itself with a cloak made of twigs and leaves.

name: wormadam-plant
biology: When BURMY evolved, its cloak became a part of this Pokémon’s body. The cloak is never shed.

name: mothim
biology: It loves the honey of flowers and steals honey collected by COMBEE.

name: combee
biology: A Pokémon formed by three others. It busily carries sweet floral honey to VESPIQUEN.

name: vespiquen
biology: Its abdomen is a honeycomb for grubs. It raises its grubs on honey collected by COMBEE.

name: pachirisu
biology: It makes fur balls that crackle with static electricity. It stores them with berries in tree holes.

name: buizel
biology: It has a flotation sac that is like an inflatable collar. It floats on water with its head out.

name: floatzel
biology: It floats using its well-developed flotation sac. It assists in the rescues of drowning people.

name: cherubi
biology: The small ball holds the nutrients needed for evolution. Apparently, it is very sweet and tasty.

name: cherrim
biology: It blooms during times of strong sunlight. It tries to make up for everything it endured as a bud.

name: shellos
biology: Its shape and coloration vary, depending on its habitat.

name: gastrodon
biology: It has a pliable body without any bones. If any part of its body is torn off, it grows right back.

name: ambipom
biology: To eat, it deftly shucks nuts with its two tails. It rarely uses its arms now.

name: drifloon
biology: A Pokémon formed by the spirits of people and Pokémon. It loves damp, humid seasons.

name: drifblim
biology: It’s drowzy in daytime, but flies off in the evening in big groups. No one knows where they go.

name: buneary
biology: It slams foes by sharply uncoiling its rolled ears. It stings enough to make a grown-up cry in pain.

name: lopunny
biology: An extremely cautious Pokémon. It cloaks its body with its fluffy ear fur when it senses danger.

name: mismagius
biology: Its cries sound like incantations. Those hearing it are tormented by headaches and hallucinations.

name: honchkrow
biology: Becoming active at night, it is known to swarm with numerous MURKROW in tow.

name: glameow
biology: It claws if displeased and purrs when affectionate. Its fickleness is very popular among some.

name: purugly
biology: It is a brazen brute that barges its way into another Pokémon’s nest and claims it as its own.

name: chingling
biology: It emits cries by agitating an orb at the back of its throat. It moves with flouncing hops.

name: stunky
biology: It protects itself by spraying a noxious fluid from its rear. The stench lingers for 24 hours.

name: skuntank
biology: It sprays a vile-smelling fluid from the tip of its tail to attack. Its range is over 160 feet.

name: bronzor
biology: Implements shaped like it were discovered in ancient tombs. It is unknown if they are related.

name: bronzong
biology: One caused a news sensation when it was dug up at a construction site after a 2,000-year sleep.

name: bonsly
biology: It prefers an arid atmosphere. It leaks water that looks like tears when adjusting its moisture level.

name: mime-jr
biology: It habitually mimics foes. Once mimicked, the foe cannot take its eyes off this Pokémon.

name: happiny
biology: It loves round white things. It carries an egg-shaped rock in imitation of CHANSEY.

name: chatot
biology: It can learn and speak human words. If they gather, they all learn the same saying.

name: spiritomb
biology: A Pokémon that was formed by 108 spirits. It is bound to a fissure in an odd keystone.

name: gible
biology: It nests in small, horizontal holes in cave walls. It pounces to catch prey that stray too close.

name: gabite
biology: There is a long-held belief that medicine made from its scales will heal even incurable illnesses.

name: garchomp
biology: When it folds up its body and extends its wings, it looks like a jet plane. It flies at sonic speed.

name: munchlax
biology: It wolfs down its weight in food once a day, swallowing food whole with almost no chewing.

name: riolu
biology: The aura that emanates from its body intensifies to alert others if it is afraid or sad.

name: lucario
biology: It has the ability to sense the auras of all things. It understands human speech.

name: hippopotas
biology: It lives in arid places. Instead of perspiration, it expels grainy sand from its body.

name: hippowdon
biology: It blasts internally stored sand from ports on its body to create a towering twister for attack.

name: skorupi
biology: It grips prey with its tail claws and injects poison. It tenaciously hangs on until the poison takes.

name: drapion
biology: It has the power in its clawed arms to make scrap of a car. The tips of its claws release poison.

name: croagunk
biology: Its cheeks hold poison sacs. It tries to catch foes off guard to jab them with toxic fingers.

name: toxicroak
biology: Its knuckle claws secrete a toxin so vile that even a scratch could prove fatal.

name: carnivine
biology: It attracts prey with its sweet- smelling saliva, then chomps down. It takes a whole day to eat prey.

name: finneon
biology: After long exposure to sunlight, the patterns on its tail fins shine vividly when darkness arrives.

name: lumineon
biology: It lives on the deep-sea floor. It attracts prey by flashing the patterns on its four tail fins.

name: mantyke
biology: A friendly Pokémon that captures the subtle flows of seawater using its two antennae.

name: snover
biology: It lives on snowy mountains. Having had little contact with humans, it is boldly inquisitive.

name: abomasnow
biology: It whips up blizzards in mountains that are always buried in snow. It is the abominable snowman.

name: weavile
biology: They live in cold regions, forming groups of four or five that hunt prey with impressive coordination.

name: magnezone
biology: It evolved from exposure to a special magnetic field. Three units generate magnetism.

name: lickilicky
biology: It wraps things with its extensible tongue. Getting too close to it will leave you soaked with drool.

name: rhyperior
biology: It puts rocks in holes in its palms and uses its muscles to shoot them. GEODUDE are shot at rare times.

name: tangrowth
biology: It ensnares prey by extending arms made of vines. Losing arms to predators does not trouble it.

name: electivire
biology: It pushes the tips of its two tails against the foe, then lets loose with over 20,000 volts of power.

name: magmortar
biology: It blasts fireballs of over 3,600 degrees F from the ends of its arms. It lives in volcanic craters.

name: togekiss
biology: It will never appear where there is strife. Its sightings have become rare recently.

name: yanmega
biology: By churning its wings, it creates shock waves that inflict critical internal injuries to foes.

name: leafeon
biology: Just like a plant, it uses photosynthesis. As a result, it is always enveloped in clear air.

name: glaceon
biology: As a protective technique, it can completely freeze its fur to make its hairs stand like needles.

name: gliscor
biology: It observes prey while hanging inverted from branches. When the chance presents itself, it swoops!

name: mamoswine
biology: Its impressive tusks are made of ice. The population thinned when it turned warm after the ice age.

name: porygon-z
biology: Additional software was installed to make it a better Pokémon. It began acting oddly, however.

name: gallade
biology: A master of courtesy and swordsmanship, it fights using extending swords on its elbows.

name: probopass
biology: It freely controls three small units called Mini-Noses using magnetic force.

name: dusknoir
biology: The antenna on its head captures radio waves from the world of spirits that command it to take people there.

name: froslass
biology: It freezes foes with an icy breath nearly -60 degrees F. What seems to be its body is actually hollow.

name: rotom
biology: Its body is composed of plasma. It is known to infiltrate electronic devices and wreak havoc.

name: uxie
biology: Known as “The Being of Knowledge.” It is said that it can wipe out the memory of those who see its eyes.

name: mesprit
biology: Known as “The Being of Emotion.” It taught humans the nobility of sorrow, pain, and joy.

name: azelf
biology: It is thought that Uxie, Mesprit, and Azelf all came from the same egg.

name: dialga
biology: It has the power to control time. It appears in Sinnoh-region myths as an ancient deity.

name: palkia
biology: It has the ability to distort space. It is described as a deity in Sinnoh-region mythology.

name: heatran
biology: It dwells in volcanic caves. It digs in with its cross-shaped feet to crawl on ceilings and walls.

name: regigigas
biology: There is an enduring legend that states this Pokémon towed continents with ropes.

name: giratina-altered
biology: A Pokémon that is said to live in a world on the reverse side of ours. It appears in an ancient cemetery.

name: cresselia
biology: Shiny particles are released from its wings like a veil. It is said to represent the crescent moon.

name: phione
biology: A Pokémon that lives in warm seas. It inflates the flotation sac on its head to drift and search for food.

name: manaphy
biology: Born on a cold seafloor, it will swim great distances to return to its birthplace.

name: darkrai
biology: It can lull people to sleep and make them dream. It is active during nights of the new moon.

name: shaymin-land
biology: It lives in flower patches and avoids detection by curling up to look like a flowering plant.

name: arceus
biology: It is told in mythology that this Pokémon was born before the universe even existed.

name: victini
biology: This Pokémon brings victory. It is said that Trainers with Victini always win, regardless of the type of encounter.

name: snivy
biology: It is very intelligent and calm. Being exposed to lots of sunlight makes its movements swifter.

name: servine
biology: It moves along the ground as if sliding. Its swift movements befuddle its foes, and it then attacks with a vine whip.

name: serperior
biology: It can stop its opponents’ movements with just a glare. It takes in solar energy and boosts it internally.

name: tepig
biology: It can deftly dodge its foe’s attacks while shooting fireballs from its nose. It roasts berries before it eats them.

name: pignite
biology: When its internal fire flares up, its movements grow sharper and faster. When in trouble, it emits smoke.

name: emboar
biology: It can throw a fire punch by setting its fists on fire with its fiery chin. It cares deeply about its friends.

name: oshawott
biology: It fights using the scalchop on its stomach. In response to an attack, it retaliates immediately by slashing.

name: dewott
biology: Strict training is how it learns its flowing double-scalchop technique.

name: samurott
biology: One swing of the sword incorporated in its armor can fell an opponent. A simple glare from one of them quiets everybody.

name: patrat
biology: Using food stored in cheek pouches, they can keep watch for days. They use their tails to communicate with others.

name: watchog
biology: When they see an enemy, their tails stand high, and they spit the seeds of berries stored in their cheek pouches.

name: lillipup
biology: It faces strong opponents with great courage. But, when at a disadvantage in a fight, this intelligent Pokémon flees.

name: herdier
biology: It has black, cape-like fur that is very hard and decreases the amount of damage it receives.

name: stoutland
biology: It rescues people stranded by blizzards in the mountains. Its shaggy fur shields it from the cold.

name: purrloin
biology: They steal from people for fun, but their victims can’t help but forgive them. Their deceptively cute act is perfect.

name: liepard
biology: These Pokémon vanish and appear unexpectedly. Many Trainers are drawn to their beautiful form and fur.

name: pansage
biology: This Pokémon dwells deep in the forest. Eating a leaf from its head whisks weariness away as if by magic.

name: simisage
biology: Ill tempered, it fights by swinging its barbed tail around wildly. The leaf growing on its head is very bitter.

name: pansear
biology: When it is angered, the temperature of its head tuft reaches 600° F. It uses its tuft to roast berries.

name: simisear
biology: It loves sweets because they become energy for the fire burning inside its body.

biology: The water stored inside the tuft on its head is full of nutrients. Plants that receive its water grow large.

name: musharna
biology: The mist emanating from their foreheads is packed with the dreams of people and Pokémon.

biology: Each follows its Trainer’s orders as best it can, but they sometimes fail to understand complicated commands.

name: tranquill
biology: It can return to its Trainer’s location regardless of the distance separating them.

name: unfezant
biology: Males swing their head plumage to threaten opponents. The females’ flying abilities surpass those of the males.

name: blitzle
biology: Its mane shines when it discharges electricity. They use their flashing manes to communicate with one another.

name: zebstrika
biology: They have lightning-like movements. When Zebstrika run at full speed, the sound of thunder reverberates.

name: roggenrola
biology: Its ear is hexagonal in shape. Compressed underground, its body is as hard as steel.

name: boldore
biology: When it overflows with power, the orange crystal on its body glows. It looks for underground water in caves.

name: gigalith
biology: Compressing the energy from its internal core lets it fire off an attack capable of blowing away a mountain.

name: woobat

name: swoobat
biology: It emits sound waves of various frequencies from its nose, including some powerful enough to destroy rocks.

name: drilbur
biology: It can dig through the ground at a speed of 30 mph. It could give a car running aboveground a good race.

name: excadrill

name: audino
biology: It touches others with the feelers on its ears, using the sound of their heartbeats to tell how they are feeling.

name: timburr

name: gurdurr
biology: This Pokémon is so muscular and strongly built that even a group of wrestlers could not make it budge an inch.

name: conkeldurr

name: leavanny

name: venipede

name: whirlipede
biology: Protected by a hard shell, it spins its body like a wheel and crashes furiously into its enemies.

name: scolipede
biology: With quick movements, it chases down its foes, attacking relentlessly with its horns until it prevails.

name: cottonee
biology: When attacked, it escapes by shooting cotton from its body. The cotton serves as a decoy to distract the attacker.

name: whimsicott
biology: Like the wind, it can slip through any gap, no matter how small. It leaves balls of white fluff behind.

name: petilil
biology: The leaves on its head are very bitter. Eating one of these leaves is known to refresh a tired body.

name: lilligant
biology: Even veteran Trainers face a challenge in getting its beautiful flower to bloom. This Pokémon is popular with celebrities.

name: basculin-red-striped
biology: Red and blue Basculin get along so poorly, they’ll start fighting instantly. These Pokémon are very hostile.

name: krokorok
biology: They live in groups of a few individuals. Protective membranes shield their eyes from sandstorms.

name: krookodile
biology: They never allow prey to escape. Their jaws are so powerful, they can crush the body of an automobile.

name: darumaka
biology: When its internal fire is burning, it cannot calm down and it runs around. When the fire diminishes, it falls asleep.

name: darmanitan-standard
biology: Its internal fire burns at 2,500° F, making enough power that it can destroy a dump truck with one punch.

name: maractus
biology: It uses an up-tempo song and dance to drive away the bird Pokémon that prey on its flower seeds.

name: dwebble
biology: This Pokémon can easily melt holes in hard rocks with a liquid secreted from its mouth.

name: crustle
biology: Competing for territory, Crustle fight viciously. The one whose boulder is broken is the loser of the battle.

name: scraggy
biology: Its skin has a rubbery elasticity, so it can reduce damage by defensively pulling its skin up to its neck.

name: scrafty
biology: Groups of them beat up anything that enters their territory. Each can spit acidic liquid from its mouth.

name: sigilyph
biology: They never vary the route they fly, because their memories of guarding an ancient city remain steadfast.

biology: Each of them carries a mask that used to be its face when it was human. Sometimes they look at it and cry.

name: cofagrigus
biology: It has been said that they swallow those who get too close and turn them into mummies. They like to eat gold nuggets.

name: tirtouga
biology: Restored from a fossil, this Pokémon can dive to depths beyond half a mile.

name: carracosta
biology: They can live both in the ocean and on land. A slap from one of them is enough to open a hole in the bottom of a tanker.

name: archen
biology: Said to be an ancestor of bird Pokémon, they were unable to fly and moved about by hopping from one branch to another.

name: archeops
biology: They are intelligent and will cooperate to catch prey. From the ground, they use a running start to take flight.

name: trubbish
biology: Inhaling the gas they belch will make you sleep for a week. They prefer unsanitary places.

name: garbodor
biology: It clenches opponents with its left arm and finishes them off with foul-smelling poison gas belched from its mouth.

name: zorua
biology: It changes into the forms of others to surprise them. Apparently, it often transforms into a silent child.

name: zoroark
biology: Stories say those who tried to catch Zoroark were trapped in an illusion and punished.

name: minccino
biology: Minccino greet each other by grooming one another thoroughly with their tails.

name: cinccino
biology: Their white fur is coated in a special oil that makes it easy for them to deflect attacks.

name: gothita
biology: Their ribbonlike feelers increase their psychic power. They are always staring at something.

name: gothorita
biology: They use hypnosis to control people and Pokémon. Tales of Gothorita leading people astray are told in every corner.

name: gothitelle
biology: Starry skies thousands of light-years away are visible in the space distorted by their intense psychic power.

name: solosis
biology: They drive away attackers by unleashing psychic power. They can use telepathy to talk with others.

name: duosion
biology: Since they have two divided brains, at times they suddenly try to take two different actions at once.

name: reuniclus
biology: When Reuniclus shake hands, a network forms between their brains, increasing their psychic power.

name: ducklett
biology: These bird Pokémon are excellent divers. They swim around in the water eating their favorite food--peat moss.

name: swanna
biology: Swanna start to dance at dusk. The one dancing in the middle is the leader of the flock.

name: vanillite
biology: The temperature of their breath is -58° F. They create snow crystals and make snow fall in the areas around them.

name: vanillish
biology: Snowy mountains are this Pokémon’s habitat. During an ancient ice age, they moved to southern areas.

name: vanilluxe
biology: Swallowing large amounts of water, they make snow clouds inside their bodies and attack their foes with violent blizzards.

name: deerling
biology: The color and scent of their fur changes to match the mountain grass. When they sense hostility, they hide in the grass.

name: sawsbuck
biology: They migrate according to the seasons. People can tell the season by looking at Sawsbuck’s horns.

name: emolga
biology: The energy made in its cheeks’ electric pouches is stored inside its membrane and released while it is gliding.

name: karrablast
biology: These mysterious Pokémon evolve when they receive electrical stimulation while they are in the same place as Shelmet.

name: escavalier
biology: They fly around at high speed, striking with their pointed spears. Even when in trouble, they face opponents bravely.

name: foongus
biology: It lures people in with its Poké Ball pattern, then releases poison spores. Why it resembles a Poké Ball is unknown.

name: amoonguss
biology: It lures prey close by dancing and waving its arm caps, which resemble Poké Balls, in a swaying motion.

name: frillish
biology: With its thin, veil-like arms wrapped around the body of its opponent, it sinks to the ocean floor.

name: jellicent
biology: The fate of the ships and crew that wander into Jellicent’s habitat: all sunken, all lost, all vanished.

name: alomomola
biology: They float upon the open sea. Many water Pokémon gather in the area around Alomomola.

name: joltik
biology: Joltik that live in cities have learned a technique for sucking electricity from the outlets in houses.

name: galvantula
biology: When attacked, they create an electric barrier by spitting out many electrically charged threads.

name: ferroseed
biology: When threatened, it attacks by shooting a barrage of spikes, which gives it a chance to escape by rolling away.

name: ferrothorn
biology: It fights by swinging around its three spiky feelers. A hit from these steel spikes can reduce a boulder to rubble.

name: klink
biology: The two minigears that mesh together are predetermined. Each will rebound from other minigears without meshing.

name: klang
biology: By changing the direction in which it rotates, it communicates its feelings to others. When angry, it rotates faster.

name: klinklang
biology: Its red core functions as an energy tank. It fires the charged energy through its spikes into an area.

name: tynamo
biology: While one alone doesn’t have much power, a chain of many Tynamo can be as powerful as lightning.

name: eelektrik
biology: They coil around foes and shock them with electricity-generating organs that seem simply to be circular patterns.

name: eelektross
biology: They crawl out of the ocean using their arms. They will attack prey on shore and immediately drag it into the ocean.

name: elgyem
biology: It uses its strong psychic power to squeeze its opponent’s brain, causing unendurable headaches.

name: beheeyem
biology: It can manipulate an opponent’s memory. Apparently, it communicates by flashing its three different-colored fingers.

name: litwick
biology: Litwick shines a light that absorbs the life energy of people and Pokémon, which becomes the fuel that it burns.

name: lampent
biology: This ominous Pokémon is feared. Through cities it wanders, searching for the spirits of the fallen.

name: chandelure
biology: It absorbs a spirit, which it then burns. By waving the flames on its arms, it puts its foes into a hypnotic trance.

name: axew
biology: They use their tusks to crush the berries they eat. Repeated regrowth makes their tusks strong and sharp.

name: fraxure
biology: Since a broken tusk will not grow back, they diligently sharpen their tusks on river rocks after they’ve been fighting.

name: haxorus
biology: They are kind but can be relentless when defending territory. They challenge foes with tusks that can cut steel.

name: cubchoo
biology: When it is not feeling well, its mucus gets watery and the power of its Ice-type moves decreases.

name: beartic
biology: It can make its breath freeze at will. Very able in the water, it swims around in northern seas and catches prey.

name: cryogonal
biology: When its body temperature goes up, it turns into steam and vanishes. When its temperature lowers, it returns to ice.

name: shelmet
biology: When attacked, it defends itself by closing the lid of its shell. It can spit a sticky, poisonous liquid.

name: accelgor
biology: When its body dries out, it weakens. So, to prevent dehydration, it wraps itself in many layers of thin membrane.

name: stunfisk
biology: Its skin is very hard, so it is unhurt even if stepped on by sumo wrestlers. It smiles when transmitting electricity.

name: mienfoo
biology: In fights, they dominate with onslaughts of flowing, continuous attacks. With their sharp claws, they cut enemies.

name: mienshao
biology: It wields the fur on its arms like a whip. Its arm attacks come with such rapidity that they cannot even be seen.

name: druddigon
biology: It warms its body by absorbing sunlight with its wings. When its body temperature falls, it can no longer move.

name: golett
biology: The energy that burns inside it enables it to move, but no one has yet been able to identify this energy.

name: golurk
biology: It flies across the sky at Mach speeds. Removing the seal on its chest makes its internal energy go out of control.

name: pawniard
biology: Blades comprise this Pokémon’s entire body. If battling dulls the blades, it sharpens them on stones by the river.

name: bisharp
biology: It leads a group of Pawniard. It battles to become the boss, but will be driven from the group if it loses.

name: bouffalant
biology: Their fluffy fur absorbs damage, even if they strike foes with a fierce headbutt.

name: rufflet
biology: They crush berries with their talons. They bravely stand up to any opponent, no matter how strong it is.

name: braviary
biology: They fight for their friends without any thought about danger to themselves. One can carry a car while flying.

name: vullaby
biology: Its wings are too tiny to allow it to fly. As the time approaches for it to evolve, it discards the bones it was wearing.

name: mandibuzz
biology: It makes a nest out of bones it finds. It grabs weakened prey in its talons and hauls it to its nest of bones.
